    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a mechanically sound 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), featuring the 3.6L M96 horizontally opposed six-cylinder engine paired with a G96 6-speed manual transaxle. This example features a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced Rear Main Seal (RMS), ensuring the longevity of the powertrain. The suspension geometry is maintained by Bilstein B6 dampers and refreshed bushings, preserving the iconic rear-engine weight bias and tactile steering feedback. Deceleration is managed by four-piston Brembo monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors. The car exhibits minor cosmetic road wear consistent with its 'good' status, but the drivetrain is exceptionally tight with linear power delivery and precise gear synchronization. A perfect candidate for a high-performance daily driver or weekend canyon car.",
